item.title: CVE-2019-14837|2024-08-05T00:26:39.127Z -- red%20hat -- keycloak
item.description: A flaw was found in keycloack before version 8.0.0. The owner of 'placeholder.org' domain can setup mail server on this domain and knowing only name of a client can reset password and then log in. For example, for client name 'test' the email address will be 'service-account-test@placeholder.org'.
